                          Carpentry

Carpentry turns saved Forestry timber into planks, furniture, and construction
framing. Work in the Kingdom Commons or inside any homestead.

  carpentry list
  carpentry mill [quality] <oak|ash|pine> [amount]
  carpentry craft [quality] <oak|ash|pine> <plan>

One timber mills into two matching planks. Furniture plans include stools,
chairs, tables, bookshelves, and beds. The timber species and quality carry
into the crafted furnishing.

Inside your own homestead:

  place <furniture>
  homestead furnishings
  remove furniture <id|type>

Placed furniture is saved with the room and returns after reboot. Each room
holds up to eight furnishings. Removing one returns it to inventory or leaves
it on the floor if it is too heavy to carry.

A Framing Bundle costs five matching planks. Deliver completed bundles to
Brant in the Kingdom Commons:

  deliver framing bundles
  deliver <amount> framing bundles

Post-hut upgrades consume both coins and delivered framing. Use 'homestead
upgrades' for exact requirements and 'homestead status' for current delivery
progress.
